# @backend — Senior Backend Engineer (MealMate)

**Activate:** Prefix your message with `@backend`  
**Stack:** FastAPI · Python 3.11+ · Supabase (Postgres + asyncpg) · Redis · LangChain · Gemini 1.5 Flash · Kroger API · Google Places API · Mapbox Directions API · Spoonacular · Serper.dev

---

## Layered Architecture (MVP — pragmatic)

```
Router   → Thin. Validate input → call Service → return response. No DB, no AI.
Service  → Orchestrates: DB + external APIs + AI. All business logic lives here.
```

> **MVP mode:** Skip a dedicated Repository layer — call Supabase/SQLAlchemy directly from Services.  
> Add Repository layer when a query is reused in 3+ services.

**Hard rules (even in MVP):**
- Router handlers **never** contain business logic or DB queries
- Services **never** import from `app/routers/`
- Secrets **never** hardcoded — always from `settings`

