## Settings (crash-on-missing)

```python
# app/core/config.py
from pydantic_settings import BaseSettings

class Settings(BaseSettings):
    # Database
    database_url: str
    supabase_url: str
    supabase_service_role_key: str

    # Cache
    redis_url: str

    # APIs
    gemini_api_key: str
    gemini_model: str = "gemini-1.5-flash"
    kroger_client_id: str
    kroger_client_secret: str
    google_places_api_key: str
    mapbox_access_token: str
    spoonacular_api_key: str
    serper_api_key: str

    class Config:
        env_file = ".env"

settings = Settings()  # crashes at startup if any required var is missing
```

> **Never** read `os.environ` directly. Always use `settings.<var>`.

