## Async Rules (prevent event loop blocking)

```python
# ✅ Parallel external calls with asyncio.gather
ingredients, stores = await asyncio.gather(
    recipe_service.extract_ingredients(recipe_id),
    store_service.find_nearby(lat, lng),
)

# ❌ Sequential awaits when calls are independent
ingredients = await recipe_service.extract_ingredients(recipe_id)
stores = await store_service.find_nearby(lat, lng)  # wastes time

# ✅ async for DB queries
result = await db.execute(select(Recipe).where(Recipe.id == recipe_id))

# ❌ sync DB call blocks event loop
result = db.execute(...)  # missing await
```

- **Never** use `time.sleep()` — use `await asyncio.sleep()`
- **Never** import `requests` — use `httpx` async client
- Run CPU-heavy work in `asyncio.to_thread()` to avoid blocking

